Load local phytoplankton cell count file

Source: R/read_importphyto.R
read_importphyto.Rd

Load local phytoplankton cell count file

read_importphyto(xlsx, download_latest = FALSE, na = "")

Arguments

xlsx

chr string path for local excel file, to overwrite if not current
download_latest

logical passed to read_dlcurrent to download raw data and compare with existing in xlsx if available
na

chr vector of strings to interpret as NA, passed to read_xlsx

Value

A data.frame of formatted water quality data.

Details

Pytoplankton cell count data downloaded from ftp://ftp.epchc.org/EPC_ERM_FTP/WQM_Reports/, file PlanktonDataList_ThroughCurrentReportMonth.xlsx

See also

read_importwq

Other read: read_chkdate(), read_dlcurrent(), read_formbenthic(), read_formfim(), read_formphyto(), read_formwq(), read_importbenthic(), read_importfim(), read_importwq()

Examples

if (FALSE) {
# file path
xlsx <- '~/Desktop/phyto_data.xlsx'

# load and assign to object
phytodata <- read_importphyto(xlsx)
}
